00:55:46.910 --> 00:55:48.060
But trust me.

00:55:48.060 --> 00:55:53.580
Don't ever do-- Like I've been on projects
where people like, "Oh, maybe we want a little

00:55:53.580 --> 00:55:55.270
bit more precision or whatever.

00:55:55.270 --> 00:55:56.810
Let's use decimeters or something."

00:55:56.810 --> 00:55:57.810
&gt;&gt;Dan G: Exactly.

00:55:57.810 --> 00:55:58.810
&gt;&gt;Ian: And it just screws up your physics
system.

00:55:58.810 --> 00:55:59.810
Don't ever use that.

00:55:59.810 --> 00:56:08.650
But define your UI in meters and then just
have a matrix that scales from meters to screen

00:56:08.650 --> 00:56:09.650
units.

00:56:09.650 --> 00:56:12.450
&gt;&gt;Dan G: and you'll definitely have to test
this on a wide variety of physical screen

00:56:12.450 --> 00:56:13.450
sizes.

